# Mycelium — Cursor Rules

## Project

Multi-agent orchestration framework. Node.js 22+, ESM modules, Express 5, Cloudflare D1/Vectorize/R2.

## Code Style

- ESM imports only (`import`/`export`). No `require()`.
- Async/await with try/catch. No callbacks.
- No TypeScript on VPS. TypeScript only in `worker/src/`.
- Plain JS with JSDoc for type hints where helpful.
- Svelte 5 runes in portal (`$state`, `$derived`, `$effect`). No Svelte 4 stores.
- Tailwind CSS + CSS custom properties. Tokens in `portal/src/lib/styles/tokens.css`.
- Geist font (sans), JetBrains Mono (mono). No serif fonts.

## Architecture

- `agent-server.js` is the single binary for all agents. Config in `agents/<id>.json`.
- `lib/db-d1.js` handles all DB access. Auto-encrypts writes, auto-decrypts reads.
- `lib/runner.js` wraps Claude CLI subprocess.
- `lib/crypto-local.js` does AES-256-GCM. Master key on VPS only.
- `worker/src/` is the Cloudflare Worker. Passthrough — no decryption capability.
- `portal/` is SvelteKit static. Do not run `npm run build` — owner deploys manually.

## Security

- Never put encryption keys in git, Worker secrets, or client code.
- Per-agent tokens (`tok_xxx_...`). Agents see only their scope.
- SQL params always use `?` placeholders. Never interpolate.
- Bots bind to 127.0.0.1, not 0.0.0.0.

## Database

- Cloudflare D1 (SQLite). Migrations in `migrations/`.
- Encrypted fields: content, thinking (messages); name, email (people); etc.
- Use `d1Query(sql, params, opts)` from `lib/db-d1.js`. Never call the Worker API directly.

## Patterns

- New MCP tool: follow `mcp/mya-tools.js` pattern.
- New agent: `npm run add-agent <id>`, then configure JSON + prompt + PM2.
- New API endpoint: add to `agent-server.js`, portal consumes via fetch.
- New migration: `migrations/NNN_descriptive_name.sql`, run via wrangler.
